summary: Coming to the end of the week, was my luck improved?
title: Coming to the end of the week, was my luck improved?
body:
As I’ve mentioned, last Monday I experienced my first ever car accident. This week I was hoping be a little more relaxing after experiencing a lot of emotional upheaval last week. I was wrong! 

Last week I organised myself a rental car as part of my insurance policy and found out once the insurance company decided my car was a write off and would be paid out, once I receive the payout, I have to return the rental car. I was advised of the write of situation last week so I wasn’t sure I’d have much time. To make the situation more urgent, I was driving to a job interview this Tuesday and was almost involved in a car accident. When I pulled over to sort the situation out, rain was pelting down and I didn’t have a coat on me! I managed to make it to the job interview (albeit a bit late) but was so stressed driving my rental car around. So on Wednesday I ventured out with my awesome Dad car shopping. I am really happy to report there is a car that stole my heart and I was lucky enough to bring my 2012 Hyundai I30 Trophy (name pending) home! Safe to say I was pretty happy and super relieved to be returning the rental car!!! 

On Thursday, I visited my doctor to get results on an xray of my foot that was injured in the accident. Completely positive results and the pain still in my foot should subside soon. Thursday afternoon I hoped all was going back to normal and I returned to one of my two roles (volunteer counsellor and paid integration aide) in a high school…. my first love, counselling! Unfortunately my afternoon didn’t improve massively. One of my clients expressed some concerns which required mandatory reporting. As it was the end of the school day, I left the necessary info with my supervisor and spoke to my client about us doing a safety plan the next morning. The catch was the mandatory report wasn’t successful because the contact numbers on the students contact section were disconnected. 

Friday rolls around and I’m ready to be productive and see the high risk student. I drove to the school with my window down and when I’d parked and went to put it up, the glass fell off the track and the window wouldn’t go up!!! I was horrified!!! I had to quickly race home and let the dealer who sold me the car know, who asked I bring the car to his yard. But I was panicked because I hadn’t been to see the student I needed to see. So I borrowed my brothers car for a moment to go back to the school and discovered the student wasn’t there yet. I waited until a short time into 2nd period and felt I needed to take advantage of the time and drop my car off so I could return back to the school and see the student. Given we didn’t have contact numbers for the students parents, it was even more important I see the student that day. Upon taking my car to the dealer, they took it to another yard to be looked at. It turned out the mechanism which makes the window go up and down broke. The car dealership owner took me back to work and I was able to pick up my car that afternoon. Luckily the student also turned up and everything was as successful as it could be in that situation. 

On Saturday I went to see my beautiful best friend, her husband and their kids who I call my nieces. They were all really happy I’d gotten another car and to know my foot was ok. They all saw me very emotional over the crash. I went to take ¾ girls out to test my car but 3 of 4, Madelyn, was too terrified to get in my car because of the crash. My stomach absolutely sunk to the ground when she said she was scared because of my car crash :( Another side effect of the crash and getting a new car has been limited money. This breaks my heart because I’d normally be really happy to get a few things for my nieces when we’re out and about, but because of lack of money, had to say no to even buying them the smallest things because I need to save if I’m going to get them anything for Christmas (their existence is my FAVOURITE thing about Christmas). 

Sunday has luckily been restful which I need before this week coming. 

Right now I’m most thankful that I bought my @taylorswift #reputationtour tickets last year so I don’t have to give up seeing Taylor this coming Friday in Melbourne!!! I’m really sad my plans to book a hotel in the city so I didn’t have to worry about driving, lack of funds to get merch and lack of funds to get my makeup specially done has been ruined by having to get another car. But more grateful I can still go! I really wanted this concert experience to be a special one because I’ll be going by myself and just really wanted to be able to treat myself to a proper experience. But at least I’ll get to see the masterpiece! Never forget how much I want to meet you!

blog.title: The Next Chapter | Chrysalis | Kaleidoscope 💫
blog.description:
Hi, I'm Kris!! || 26 || DR || Swiftie since '07 || Rep Tour - Melbourne Oct '18 + Brisbane Nov '18 || 1989 Tour - Brisbane Dec '15 || 
My primary tumblr is "moonlightandguitars", so if I might follow you from there 💕

body:
Five days

Five days until I fly cross country to Melbourne, Victoria, Australia.

Five days until I put on the “costume” I made for the (official) first time.

Five days until I drag my fiance to Marvel Stadium, hours before the concert.

Five days until I meet so many beautiful, like minded, kind hearted Swifties.

Five days until I feel that electricity again that I felt in 2015. That captivating emotion of anticipation and excitement. That enthralling, all encompassing jitteriness that only comes from knowing your idol is going to be within a few (hundred) meters of you.

Five days until I see Taylor Swift once again. Five days until I hear her live once more. Five days.

Five! Days! @taylorswift @taylornation

summary: The number one feeling I felt in the whole relationship was anxiety. Because it felt very fragile, it felt very tentative. And...
text: The number one feeling I felt in the whole relationship was anxiety. Because it felt very fragile, it felt very tentative. And it always felt like, ‘Okay, what’s the next road block? What’s the next thing that’s gonna deter this? How long do we have before this turns into just an awful mess and we break up? Is it a month? Is it three days? And so, you know, I think a lot of relationships can be very solid and that’s kind of what you hope for, for it to be solid and healthy, but that’s not always what you get. And it doesn’t mean that it’s not… special and extraordinary just to have a relationship that’s fragile and somehow meaningful in that fragility.
source: Taylor Swift, Out of the Woods speech in the Grammy Museum.

body: Hi @taylorswift ! This week has been crazy: I had my dance concert this weekend and I see you on Friday! I just wanted to let you know that over the weekend I won a massive and prestigious dance award, one that I never thought that I would actually receive. I’m still in shock honestly. Dance is a huge part of my life, and to receive something like this is insane. I have been a dancer for 12 years, almost as long as I have been a fan of you. I could not think of a better way to finish October off than to win this and see you on Friday, I cannot wait ❤️
